# README Update Rule

Before every commit and push, check whether the changes affect anything documented in the project README.md. If they do, update the README as part of the same commit.

Things that should trigger a README update:
- New directories or significant files added to the project structure
- New API endpoints, MCP tools, or CLI commands
- Changes to prerequisites, installation steps, or environment setup
- New features, capabilities, or integrations
- Changes to the tech stack (new dependencies, runtime changes)
- Removal of documented features or formats

Do not ask whether to update — just include it if needed.
